@startuml State_Notification
title Feature 10 - Notification Lifecycle State Machine

skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor #141417
    FontColor #FFFFFF
    BorderColor #333333
    ArrowColor #FF5C00
}

[*] --> Created : NotificationService.send()\n/ persist to DB

Created : Notification record saved
Created : Channels being resolved
Created --> Queued : Channels determined,\ndelivery dispatched

Queued : In delivery pipeline
Queued : Parallel channel dispatch
Queued --> Delivered : All channels\nsuccessfully delivered
Queued --> PartiallyDelivered : Some channels failed\n/ log failures,\n schedule retry

PartiallyDelivered : At least one channel\ndelivered
PartiallyDelivered --> Delivered : Retry succeeds\n(all channels complete)
PartiallyDelivered --> Delivered : Max retries reached\n/ mark as delivered\n with partial flag

Delivered : sent_at = now()
Delivered : Visible in notification center
Delivered --> Read : User taps/clicks\n/ read = true,\n read_at = now()

Delivered --> Dismissed : User dismisses banner\n/ dismissed_at = now()

Read : User has seen it
Read --> Dismissed : User dismisses\n(banner only)

Dismissed : Banner hidden
Dismissed --> [*] : Cleanup job\n(90 days, if read)

Read --> [*] : Cleanup job\n(90 days)

@enduml
